  "subject": "Use wait-for-dependencies in drools-apps CSIT",
  "commit_message": "Use wait-for-dependencies in drools-apps CSIT\n\nRevised drools-apps yml to conform the pattern used for api, pap,\nand the other policy repos.  In particular, deleted the port check\nfrom the setup script and replaced it with docker wait-for-dependency.\nWith this approach, the docker containers are brought up in stages\nso that dependencies are met (i.e., doesn't bring up drools until\nthe mariadb server is listening on its port).  The net result is\nthat the CSIT runs much faster.\n\nIssue-ID: POLICY-2434\nChange-Id: I7be2c7e7595cdc1541729a9675255b379565ff2e\nSigned-off-by: Jim Hahn <jrh3@att.com>\n",
